         <div xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953"><!-- p2l1-r4 -->
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Hd1e108">Rubrica 4</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De innocentia</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="21"/>
      ¶ De innocentia. Rubrica. 4
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>Tob histo. c. 22. <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e123">Saluabitur
        <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>imocens. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e129">
               <lb ed="#V" n="24"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e133">¶ Psalmista 36 psalmus Custodi in
        <lb ed="#V" n="25" break="no"/>nocentiam et vide equitatem. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e140"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e142"> psalmus. 83
        <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>Non priuabit bonis eos: qui ambulant in
        <lb ed="#V" n="27"/>inocentia dominus virtutum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e150">
               <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e154">¶ Tobias. c. 4. Quod ab alio odis fieri tibi:
        <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>inde ne alteri tum aliquandam facias. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e160">
               <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e164">¶ Uirgilius enide li. 7. ante medium: Mille
        <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>nocendi artes. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e170">
               <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e174">¶ Tullius tusculanarum questionum li. 3 In
        <lb ed="#V" n="33" break="no"/>nocentia est affectio talis animi quai noceat nemi. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e180">
               <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e184">¶ Ouidius de arte amandi li. i. Fraus absit
        <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>vacuas credis habere manus. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e190">
               <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e194">¶ Quintilianus declam. 12 declam. Male
        <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>heret ibi nocentia: vbi in potestate est secre
        <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>tum scelus. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e203">
               <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e207">¶ Mattheus in euang. c. 27. Dixit iudeis pi
        <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>latus: quid faciam de iesu qui dicitur christus. Di
        <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>cunt oes: crucifigatur. Ait illis pilatus: Quid
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>enim mali fecit: At illi magis clamabant di
        <lb ed="#V" n="43" break="no"/>centes: crucifigatur. Uidens autem pilatus quia
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>nil proficeret: sed magis tumultus fieret: ac
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>ce pta aqua lauit manus suas coram populo: <!--79.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>dicens: Innocens ego sum a sanguine iusti
        <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>huius: vos videritis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e232">
               <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e236">¶ Seneca tragediarum in edipo. c. 14. et finali
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>Nemo fit fato nocens. In hercule hetheo.
        <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>c. 8. Haud est nocens quicuque non sponte est no
        <lb ed="#V" n="51" break="no"/>cens. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e246"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e248"> Idem epistolarum ad lucillum lib.
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>18. e. 5. Securitatis magna portio est: nihil
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>inique facere. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e256">
               <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e260">¶ Lex diges. ti. de operis noui nunci. li. de pupil
        <lb ed="#V" n="55" break="no"/>lo. §. si plurium. Non debet nocere factum alte
        <lb ed="#V" n="56" break="no"/>rius: ei qui nihil fecit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e268"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e270"> Tit. de aqua plu. ar.
        <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>l. i. §. item ait: Aquam prodesse sibi vnusquisque
        <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>dum alii non nocet nec prohibetur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e278"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e280"> Ti. de iniu
        <lb ed="#V" n="59" break="no"/>riis. l. iniuriarum. §. i. Iuris executio non ha
        <lb ed="#V" n="60"/>bet iniuriam. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e289">
               <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e293">¶ Marcialis cocus li. vndique suscepto. c. 2.
        <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>Te video solum dum possis aule nocere:
        <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>Nec prodesse tamen: sed petis vt noceas. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e301">
               <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e305">¶ Auctor li. formule honeste vite. c. 5. Ama
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>bis deum: si illum in hoc imitabis vt velis omni
        <lb ed="#V" n="66" break="no"/>bus prodesse nulli nocere: et tunc te iustum virum
        <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>appellabunt omnes: sequentur venerabuntur et dili
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>gent: sicque merito iustus appellaberis. Iu
        <lb ed="#V" n="69" break="no"/>stus vt sis non solum non nocebis: sed etiam
        <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>nocentes prohibebis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e322">
               <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e326">¶ Ambrosius de officiis li. 2. c. Uitam beatam
        <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>efficiunt tranquillitas conscientie et securitas
        <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>innocentie. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e334"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e336"> Li. 3. c. 5. Non latebra sapienti
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>spes impunitatis est: sed innocentia. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e342">
               <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e346">¶ Cecilius firmianus de beata vita libro. 3
        <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>Inter summas hominis virtutes innocentia nu
        <lb ed="#V" n="77" break="no"/>meratur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e354"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e356"> Li. 4. In hoc iustitie summa consi
        <lb ed="#V" n="78"/>stit: vt non factas alteri quicquid ipsi ab al
        <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>tero pati nolis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e365">
               <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e369">¶ Augustinus in epig. prosper. emp. i. Inno
        <lb ed="#V" n="81" break="no"/>centia vera est: que nec sibi nec alteri nocet. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e375">
               <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e379">/ Emp. 75. Parum est nemini nocere: nisi
        <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>studeatur multis prodeste. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e385">
               <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e389">¶ Prosper sub vlt. c. Insontem vitam pacis a
        <lb ed="#V" n="85" break="no"/>mator agit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e395">
               <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e399">¶ Cassiodorus epistolarum li. 6. c. 16. Innocentia
        <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>cucta commendat. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e405"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e407"> Li. 9. e. 2. Uix audet quis
        <lb ed="#V" n="88" break="no"/>que in illos excedere: in quibus culpas non po
        <lb ed="#V" n="89"/>test inuenire. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e415"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e417"> Epistola. 3. Honesta sunt lucra
        <lb ed="#V" n="90"/>per que nemo leditur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e424"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e426"> Epistola. 10. Nullum le¬ <!--80.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="27-r"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>dit obseruata iustitia. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e438"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e440"> Li. 11. e. 8. In qua
        <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>parte habet homo proficere: si innocentiam pro
        <lb ed="#V" n="3" break="no"/>batus fuerit amisisse. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-d1e448">
               <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d19953-Qd1e452">¶ Baldo. 32. fabula: In te quicquid odis fie
        <lb ed="#V" n="5" break="no"/>ri molumine quo vis. Cuilibet arte mali
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>caueas inferre sodali.
        <lb ed="#V" n="7"/>Bernardus li. de improbatione vitiorum. c. 3
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>Uir sapiens prodesse cupit nec ledere quemquam
        <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>Mitibus et gratis: nemo nocere solet. </quote>
            </p>
         </div>
